A two-year-old child died while several other people were injured in accident in Mikinduri area, Meru county, on Saturday. A school bus in which wedding guests were travelling overturned at Kiuriine as they headed to Mukothima in Tharaka South. Mikinduri senior chief Jacob Mutiga told the Star that the driver lost control while trying to negotiate a sharp corner downhill. He said the accident took place shortly after he picked a woman at Kiuriine. Witnesses said the driver may have lost control while trying to avoid potholes. One added: "The corner is very sharp. The government should expand the road and fill the potholes." Deputy county commissioner Patrick Muli said the casualties were taken to Meru Teaching and Referral hospital. Click here for the latest political news